The paper discusses array data storage and processing, which is a topic that falls under the database (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the identification of a reduced set of array operators to form the foundation for an array query language, which is a topic that falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) and software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. Lastly, the paper surveys real systems for array processing, which is a topic that falls under the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
